#FUNDAMENTAL LIBRARY COMPONENT DOCUMENTATION


###Action Bar
The Action Bar component displays at the top of the page, and includes the page’s title, description, back button and action buttons.

####Usage
**Use the Action Bar if:**

**Do not use the Action Bar if:**

####Types
•	**Default**
This Action Bar displays a page title, description, back button and action buttons.
•	**No back button**
This Action Bar doesn’t display a back button, but displays a page title, description and action buttons.
•	**No description**
This Action Bar doesn’t display a description, but displays a page title, back button, and action buttons.
•	**Long page title and description**
This Action Bar displays a long page title and description, as well as a back button and action buttons.
•	**Contextual menu**
This Action Bar displays a page title and contextual menu with several main actions.
•	**Responsive [M-L]**
This Action Bar is responsive, and displays a page title, description, back button and action buttons. 
o	Note: the responsive feature fits the M and L sizes required for tablet and small desktop screens.
•	**Responsive [XL]**
This Action Bar is responsive, and displays a page title, description, back button and action buttons.
o	Note: the responsive feature fits the XL size required for larger screens of 1440px or more.
•	**Mobile**
This Action Bar is mobile responsive, and displays a page title, description, back button and action buttons.

###Avatar
The Avatar component displays an image, icon or user initials, and is used for user profiles, placeholder images, icons or business-related images i.e. product photos.

####Sizes 

**Size | rem	| Use for images in…	| Modifier**
-----|------|---------------------|----------------------------
XS	| 2 rem	| Table list items, Card list items | --xs modifier
S	| 3 rem	| Card headers, Card list items | --s modifier
M	| 4 rem	| App headers for small screen sizes | --m modifier
L	| 5 rem	| App headers for normal screen sizes | --l modifier
XL | 7 rem | App headers for large screen sizes | --xl modifier

####Usage
**Use Avatar to display:**
•	A user’s image or initials
•	Standardized images for business-related content (such as products, company logos, ad campaign images etc.)
•	Icons
•	Images with a transparent background
•	Placeholder images

**Do not use Avatar if:**
•	You want to display an image for any other use case. Instead, use the Image component.
•	You want to display images in a carousel. Instead, use the Carousel component.
•	You want to display an interactive icon. Instead, use the Button component with an icon inside.


####Types
•	**Icon**
Include role="presentation" when the avatar is used for only illustrative purposes. For example, include role if the icon sits right next to a label.
•	**Initials**
Include aria-label when there is no text equivalent for the avatar. This isn’t necessary if the avatar is used for illustrative purposes only. See Icon above.
•	**Circle**
A circle style can be displayed using the --circle modifier.
•	**Background image**
A background image can be displayed using the --thumbnail modifier.
•	**Transparent**
A transparent style can be displayed using the --transparent modifier.
•	**Placeholder background**
An Avatar with a placeholder background can be displayed using the --placeholder modifier.
•	**Tile icon background**
An Avatar with a tile icon background can be displayed using the --tile modifier.
•	**Accent colors**
Use fd-avatar--accent-color-* classes to change the background colors. Options include numbers ranging from 1 to 10. For example: fd-avatar--accent-color-10
•	**Zoom icon**
A zoom icon Avatar can be displayed by adding the .fd-avatar__zoom-icon element.
•	**Borders**
Borders can be displayed with the --border modifier.

